        "Support Life Foundation has earned a <cite id=\"10\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, the highest level of recognition for nonprofit data sharing. This transparency is backed by <cite id=\"11\">audited financial statements</cite> and a commitment to meeting all <cite id=\"12\">20 BBB Wise Giving Alliance Standards</cite> for Charity Accountability. Their programmatic reach is particularly notable for a mid-sized organization, managing complex initiatives like the <cite id=\"2\">Health Center Yaound\u00e9 and the Teacher For Every Village program</cite> across multiple continents."
      ],
      "summary": "Support Life Foundation is a community-based organization established in <cite id=\"1\">2017</cite> with a mission focused on social and economic justice. The organization operates a diverse range of programs including <cite id=\"2\">You Are Not Alone (YANA), Hot Meals, and Project Educate</cite>, reaching communities in the <cite id=\"3\">United States, Sierra Leone, and Cameroon</cite>. Financially, the foundation demonstrates a lean operational model, reporting <cite id=\"4\">total revenue of $1,228,678</cite> in the 2023 fiscal year. A defining characteristic of the organization is its commitment to direct service delivery, maintaining a <cite id=\"5\">program expense ratio of 95.1%</cite>, which ensures that the vast majority of donor contributions are utilized for frontline initiatives rather than administrative overhead. Furthermore, the organization exhibits <cite id=\"6\">exceptional fundraising efficiency</cite>, spending $0.00 to raise every $1 in contributions. While the foundation has achieved significant growth since its founding, it currently maintains a <cite id=\"7\">76/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting a balance between high programmatic output and areas for governance enhancement.",
